{"name":"Ebon Evoker","content":"<h1 style=\"margin-top:var(--space-l);margin-bottom:var(--space-s);width:643.891px;font-family:var(--serif)\">Ebon Evoker</h1>\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\"><strong>Rarity</strong> Common</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong> You must have a class that grants you the Cast a Spell activity at level 1.</p>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight);margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\" />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\">You’ve paid a price to see beyond the darkness and return with shreds of magical knowledge from beyond the veil that risk to rip you apart if you dare release them without forethought.</p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px;font-family:var(--serif)\">@Compendium[Ebon-Evoker.items.UlmlSYUqcCGQIOY3]{Ebon Evoker Dedication}</h2>\n<p style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong>  Ebon Affect</p>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight);margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\" />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\">You have proven you bear enough resilience and responsibility to carry the onus of your terrible knowledge. You gain access to the @Compendium[Ebon-Evoker.items.SlQMT4UlFqKb8Oxh]{Ebon Infusion} action and may use it once per day. At 5th level and every 4 levels thereafter you may use Ebon Infusion an additional time per day.</p>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight);margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\" />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\"><strong>Special</strong> You can't select another dedication feat before gaining two other feats from this archetype.</p>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight);margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\" />\n<h3 style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px;font-family:var(--sans-serif)\">Ebon Evoker Adjustments</h3>\n<p style=\"width:643.891px\">Your class functions as normal but you lose your voice and gain a familiar, or enhance your familiar if you would already receive one. The changes to your character and class are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\">You cannot willingly speak except to provide verbal components to spells or fulfill the spoken portion of spells with the linguistic trait. However, you are not without a way to communicate. </li>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\">You gain a familiar (Pathfinder Second Edition Core Rulebook). While this familiar is within your reach you can choose to speak through it normally using your voice. When you speak through your familiar, you use your skills as normal for any verbal actions or activities, such as Make an Impression or Impersonate to imitate a voice. If you grant this familiar the speech familiar ability, it can talk in your stead anywhere within 50 feet of you. If you already gain a familiar at level 1 from your class, this familiar gains the speech familiar ability, which does not count against its number of chosen abilities. Your familiar shares your ebon shade and is obviously linked to you in some way</li>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\"> You become cloaked in an ebon shade, your features are cloaked in a dark veil that only your own eyes and the eyes of other ebon evokers can see through. You still appear as a unique individual with features unique to your veil, but your true face is hidden. Your eyes glow with a dim light that allows you to pierce the veil of other ebon evokers. Creatures under the effects of true seeing can pierce the veil and see your true face, treating your counteract level as half your level rounded up, and your spell DC as the counteract DC.</li>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\"> If you are forced (such as by an effect or condition) to speak, babble, or otherwise vocalize outside of the providence of the spell you are casting, you are wracked with a destabilizing force that threatens to destroy you. When you do so you take 1d4 persistent mental damage per 2 levels you possess (minimum 1d4). This mental damage cannot be reduced by any means. If you are in an area of silence or anti-magic (such as from a silence or antimagic field spell) you do not trigger this effect.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additional Feats: <strong>4th</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.BWomK7EVY0WXxWgh]{Reach Spell}, @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.FoWO4RnHRwfEIC7Q]{Widen Spell};<strong> 6th</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.DS0XlHfi3ztb3ET7]{Split Shot}; <strong>8th</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.bVng7Mkrj4UnQzLo]{Burning Spell}; <strong>20th</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.NvEYf0jIETEu2LtP]{Echoing Spell}</p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px;font-family:var(--serif)\">@Compendium[Ebon-Evoker.items.y5waOyasspFcXw4r]{Ebon Warp} 4th</h2>\n<p style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong> Ebon Evoker Dedication</p>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight);margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\" />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\">You have learned to bend spells to your whim. When you cast a spell modified by Ebon Infusion with an area and no duration, you may include an additional number of 5-foot spaces equal to the number of ebon evoker feats you have. These spaces must be contiguous with the original area of the spell. In place of adding a space, you may remove a 5-foot space from the area of the spell, causing any creature within that space that is not within another affected space to not suffer the effects of the spell.</p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px;font-family:var(--serif)\">@Compendium[Ebon-Evoker.items.tifNXDs02LQKstfc]{Terrifying Veil} 6th</h2>\n<p style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong> Ebon Evoker Dedication</p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\">You invoke the dark mystery of your ebon veil targeting foes in a 15-foot cone. Creatures that gaze into your veil must attempt a Will save against your spell DC. Regardless of the result of their save, targets are immune to your Terrifying Veil for 24 hours.</p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Critical Success </strong>The creature is unaffected.</li>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Success </strong>The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 1}</li>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Failure </strong>The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 2}</li>\n<li style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Critical Failure </strong>The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 2} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stunned]{Stunned 1} by its fear of the unknown</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px;font-family:var(--serif)\">@Compendium[Ebon-Evoker.items.iWsEyuQFwdhxcGZc]{Dark Stillness} Feat 8</h2>\n<p style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong> Ebon Evoker Dedication</p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\"><strong>Frequency </strong>once per day</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\"><strong>Requirements </strong>You are suffering from persistent mental damage caused by your ebon evoker adjustments.</p>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight);margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\" />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\">You steady your mind, this counts as having provided particularly effective aid to yourself to end your persistent mental damage. If you are still affected by a spell or condition that could force you to speak, you may attempt to Counteract it, using half your level rounded up as your counteract level and your spell attack modifier as your counteract modifier.</p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px;font-family:var(--serif)\">@Compendium[Ebon-Evoker.items.6z1qS1tfYrQbClTD]{Speak the Words} Feat 12</h2>\n<p style=\"width:643.891px\"><strong>Prerequisites</strong> Ebon Evoker Dedication</p>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight);margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\" />\n<p style=\"margin-top:var(--p-space,1em);width:643.891px\"><strong>Frequency </strong>once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You force yourself to speak, unleashing the energies of the secrets you hold deep within you on yourself and others, causing you to take persistent mental damage from your ebon evoker adjustments. Creatures in a 30-foot emanation take persistent force damage equal to the amount of persistent mental damage you suffer from this act (basic Fortitude save against your spell DC).</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"wJlZYfbdjdvT8g1Z":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.28YnW7eTex1d72Ed"}},"_id":"94XJXQr6ijAEWH3t"}
